<HEAD>Ershad Presidency to be Limited to 10 Years</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By EARLEEN FISHER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 President <PERSON> Hussain </PERSON> <PERSON> Mohammad </PERSON> <PERSON> Ershad </PERSON>, who took power in a bloodless coup in 1982, has proposed a constitutional amendment limiting the presidency to 10 years. The proposed amendment was presented to parliament Thursday, where it is assured of passage because <PERSON> Ershad </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> Jatiya </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> holds 251 of the 300 seats. `` I am certain that they -LRB- the legislators -RRB- are going to pass it, so it is good from my side and I am certain it is good for our country,'' the 59-year-old former army general said. <PERSON> Ershad </PERSON> resigned from the army in 1985 and a year later was elected to a five-year presidential term in national balloting that political opponents and foreign observers said was tainted by widespread vote fraud. Under the proposed amendment, <PERSON> Ershad </PERSON> can seek re-election in 1991 to another 5-year term but he would be banned from seeking a third term. <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION> has had nine presidents since it won independence from <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> in 1971. Each took office through military intervention, either through coup and assassination or through installation of civilians who heeded the army's dictates. <PERSON> Ershad </PERSON>, who has governed <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION> longer than any other leader, said the decision to limit the term of the president was part of his effort to modernize the nation. `` We have to prove to the world that <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION> is something more than a poor country,'' <PERSON> Ershad </PERSON> said. <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION>, whose 110 million people have an average annual income of only $ 160, is perennially buffeted by floods, cyclones, tornadoes and drought.
