he <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. The defendants' first trial ended in December 1985 with acquittals. However, after Mrs. <PERSON> Aquino </PERSON> took power in February 1986, the <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> overturned the original verdict and ordered a new trial. Brig. Gen. <PERSON> Rogelio </PERSON> <PERSON> Estacio </PERSON>, the <PERSON> Villamor </PERSON> commander, denied the prisoners were allowed to leave their quarters, but he said controls had been tightened. `` Before, we checked the roll at 7 o'clock in the evening,'' he told reporters. `` Now, we do it every three hours.'' The retrial began in April 1987. A total of 37 people are accused of the murder, but six are free on bail or under house arrest.
