<HEAD>Vietnam Population Grows to 64 Million</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> announced its population has grown to 64.4 million, and it called on all families to have no more than two children. The official <ORGANIZATION> Vietnam </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agency </ORGANIZATION> said the population had grown by 11.7 million since the last census in 1979, representing a high annual growth rate of 2.13 percent. An editorial in the <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>'s newspaper, <PERSON> Nhan </PERSON> <PERSON> Dan </PERSON>, urged all people to observe the national target of one or two children per family, the agency said. <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>'s already high and rapidly growing population has emerged as a major problem for the country, which faces large-scale unemployment, a poor social and economic infrastructure and difficulties in feeding its current population. The most populous city in <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> is <LOCATION> Ho </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Chi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Minh </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> with 3.9 million people, according to the census, conducted April 1. <LOCATION> Hanoi </LOCATION>, the capital, has 3.1 million. The census also showed there were 2,432 people _ 1,728 women and 704 men _ over the age of 100.
