<HEAD>Tons of Mail Found at Letter Carrier's Home</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOULDER, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Postal inspectors used wheelbarrows to remove two tons of mail and a half-ton of postal equipment from the yard of a letter carrier, officials said. The seizure occurred Thursday, after neighbors complained about bags of paper and reams of bulk mail in the yard. Postal Service officials would not release the carrier's name, but said he had worked for the <ORGANIZATION> Postal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> for 15 years. Inspectors said they had no idea why the carrier had been stashing the mail, but said he may face federal charges. Investigators worked for hours Thursday to remove the mail and equipment from the yard. They took the mail to the bulk mail center to determine what can still be delivered.
