 <ORGANIZATION> Adolph </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said it will offer a lower-priced beer starting Sept. 11, for the first time in its 116-year history. The brewer, the nation's fourth-largest, plans a large advertising campaign to introduce <ORGANIZATION> Keystone </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Keystone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Light </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Willey </PERSON>, brand development manager for <ORGANIZATION> Keystone </ORGANIZATION>, said Thursday. <ORGANIZATION> Coors </ORGANIZATION> will brew <ORGANIZATION> Keystone </ORGANIZATION> at its Golden plant with existing employees, <PERSON> Willey </PERSON> said. Production on other labels will not be cut. Beer pricing is divided into categories: import; super premiums such as <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Killian </PERSON>'s; premiums such as <ORGANIZATION> Miller </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Life </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Coors </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Budweiser </ORGANIZATION>; popular brands such as <ORGANIZATION> Old </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Milwaukee </ORGANIZATION>, Old Style, <PERSON> Rainier </PERSON>, and economy brands such as <PERSON> Meisterbrau </PERSON>. Popular and economy beers account for a fourth of the $ 40 billion retail beer market in the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> every year. `` There's considerable demand for a high-quality beer at a popular price. It's a category we have n't been in,'' <PERSON> Willey </PERSON> said. `` Old <LOCATION> Milwaukee </LOCATION> and <PERSON> Heileman </PERSON> are losing their market share. We think they're vulnerable,'' he added. <PERSON> Emanuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Goldman </PERSON>, an analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Paine-Webber </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>, said <ORGANIZATION> Coors </ORGANIZATION>' strategy makes se