<HEAD>High Voltage Raises Offer for Universal</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 High <ORGANIZATION> Voltage </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Engineering </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, which has been pursuing Milwaukee-based <ORGANIZATION> Universal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foods </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> since last year, announced today it was willing to raise its offer to $ 42 a share. <PERSON> Laurence </PERSON> <PERSON> Levy </PERSON>, chairman of High Voltage, based in <LOCATION> Burlington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mass. </LOCATION>, said his company delivered a letter to <ORGANIZATION> Universal </ORGANIZATION>'s board of directors, offering to buy the company in a negotiated transaction. `` We are attempting to negotiate with them because we think that is a better route,'' said <PERSON> Evan </PERSON> <PERSON> Zeppos </PERSON>, a spokesman for High Voltage in <LOCATION> Milwaukee </LOCATION>. High Voltage currently has a $ 38 per share cash tender offer for Universal, but only about 30 percent of the stockholders have tendered their shares, according to a statement last week from Universal. `` We remain committed to the acquisition of Universal,'' the letter from High Voltage said. `` We would like to meet with you at your earliest convenience to complete the negotiation of the merger agreement.'' A Universal spokeswoman said the company had no immediate response to the offer. High Voltage began its quest for Universal last December with an offer of $ 30.50 per share. The proposal, however, has been rejected by <ORGANIZATION> Universal </ORGANIZATION>'s board of directors. High Voltage challenged an anti-takeover law in <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION> that essentially blocks bidders from making direct contact with shareholders unless the company's management approves. The law was upheld this year by the <ORGANIZATION> 7th </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <OR